JOHANNESBURG - Young artists looking for inspiration can find it at the exhibition "Young Now" at the Hazard Gallery in Johannesburg's Maboneng Precinct.The work of 14 up-and-coming Southern African artists is being showcased and ranges from sculpture to printmaking and photography. The gallery's director, Jonathan Freemantle, hopes the exhibition gives emerging artists a platform to grow their work.*Watch the video above for the full storyeNCA